patch level, and the inference resolution can be adjusted to balance prediction granularity and real-time perception constraints. We study how best to adapt a ViT to our task and environment, and find that some lightweight architectures can yield good single-image segmentations at a usable frame rate, even on CPU. The resulting perception model is used as the backbone for a simple yet robust visual servoing agent, which we deploy on a differential drive mobile robot to perform two tasks: lane following and obstacle avoidance.", "authors": [{"author": {"author_id": "b932305a2f2c07917110ea8e9a5aadb3", "name": "Miguel Saavedra-Ruiz", "links": [{"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2104447076"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2314691096"}, {"type": "xplore", "link": "37089376248"}]}, "affiliations": [{"institution_id": "4a1adaf20e59d28f06de32f5adc8c2f8", "name": "DIRO, Mila - Quebec AI Institute, Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al, Montreal, Canada", "category": "unknown"}]}, {"author": {"author_id": "9127fa48bf2c74e10f7a901809673c19", "name": "Sacha Morin", "links": [{"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "1812330511"}, {"type": "xplore", "link": "37088809184"}]}, "affiliations": [{"institution_id": "4a1adaf20e59d28f06de32f5adc8c2f8", "name": "DIRO, Mila - Quebec AI Institute, Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al, Montreal, Canada", "category": "unknown"}]}, {"author": {"author_id": "f7755e3792a26b14d79e8804ff7c530f", "name": "Liam Paull", "links": [{"type": "!semantic_scholar", "link": "147812093"}, {"type": "bio", "link": "liam-paull"}, {"type": "email.mila", "link": "paulll@mila.quebec"}, {"type": "mag", "link": "2198295625"}, {"type": "mag", "link": "2873594279"}, {"type": "openreview", "link": "~Liam_Paull1"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2265536920"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2276201926"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2294873530"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "3198259"}, {"type": "wpid_en", "link": "27832"}, {"type": "wpid_f